        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Liverpool, or 7 miles south of Alvin. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Pearland, southern League City, Texas City, Friendswood,
Alvin, Dickinson, La Marque, Santa Fe, Hitchcock, southeastern
Manvel, Hillcrest, Liverpool, Bonney, and Chocolate Bayou.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
